  "notes": "First Nation straddles Ontario and Manitoba border. Large increase in accumulated surplus ($41.75M from $16.64M) driven primarily by recognition of $29.26M in prior year deferred revenue offset by new deferrals of $17.76M. Major capital construction activity: Water Treatment Plant ($25.57M in construction in progress), new houses ($672K), and daycare ($85K). New school being built off-balance sheet via Shibogama Tribal Council ($13.6M expended by year end). Consolidated entity includes CMHC Housing. FNFTA filing deadline not met as audit was completed after July 29, 2021. ISC represents 30% of revenue (down from 39%). OSR calculated as total revenue minus all government transfers ($34,632,902 - $19,407,214 = $15,225,688)."
